# .voxindexingignore — Controls what the Vox corpus indexer, Scientia ingest,
# and MENS training pipeline include when crawling the repository.
#
# This file is additive on top of .voxignore (which governs AI context exclusion).
# Files excluded here are NOT sent to the indexer but ARE still visible to human
# contributors and the compiler.
#
# SSOT: edit this file; run `vox ci sync-ignore-files` to propagate.
# See: docs/src/architecture/multi-repo-context-isolation-research-2026.md
# Inspired by: warpdotdev/warp .warpindexingignore (design reference, ADR-026)

# === BUILD & GENERATED ARTIFACTS ===
target/
dist/
build/
node_modules/
.vox_modules/
**/*.wasm
**/*.lock
Cargo.lock

# === BINARY AND MEDIA ASSETS ===
**/*.png
**/*.jpg
**/*.jpeg
**/*.gif
**/*.webp
**/*.svg
**/*.ico
**/*.woff
**/*.woff2
**/*.ttf
**/*.otf
**/*.mp4
**/*.mov
**/*.bin
**/*.safetensors
**/*.gguf
**/*.ggml
resources/

# === CORPUS & TRAINING DATA (avoid self-indexing) ===
# These are the *output* of indexing, not inputs to it.
crates/vox-corpus/data/
crates/vox-mens/data/
crates/vox-tensor/data/

# === ARCHIVED / TOMBSTONED CODE ===
# AGENTS.md §Archival Protocol — never index these.
archive/
docs/src/archive/

# === SECRETS AND CREDENTIALS ===
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.p12
**/.env
**/.env.*
crates/vox-clavis/fixtures/

# === LARGE GENERATED DOCS ===
# Avoid double-indexing rendered output; source markdown is already indexed.
docs-astro/dist/
docs/book/

# === THIRD-PARTY VENDORED CODE (index root, not subtrees) ===
# Vendored crates are indexed at Cargo.toml level only; source trees are
# redundant with crates.io metadata.
# (uncomment as vendored crates are added per ADR-026)
# crates/vox-sum-tree/src/
